## When to use
When you need to identify which processes are consuming the most bandwidth on your system and want to analyze real-time network traffic.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to execute the `nethog` command, which categorizes network usage by process. This approach allows for monitoring individual network traffic contributions from different applications or services running on your system, aiding in troubleshooting high bandwidth usage issues.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "nethogs -v 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run a shell command that displays detailed information about each process’s network activity at one-second intervals, providing real-time monitoring capabilities.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure necessary utilities like `nethogs` are installed on your system.
- Be cautious about interpreting output correctly with multiple processes running concurrently.